\title{Chu's construction}

\p{Let #{\calV} be a finitely [complete] [autonomous category](math-002S) and fix some object #{\bot}.}

\p{The objects of #{\calV_\bot} will be triples #{(V,V',v)} for #{V,V'} objects of #{\calV} and #{v:V\otimes V'\to \bot} an arrow in #{\calV}. The morphisms of #{\calV_\bot} will be pairs #{(f,f'):(V,V'v)\to (W,W',w)} where #{f:V\to W} and #{f':W'\to V'} such that the following diagram commutes:}
    \quiver{% https://q.uiver.app/#q=WzAsNCxbMCwwLCJWXFxvdGltZXMgVyciXSxbMCwxLCJXXFxvdGltZXMgVyciXSxbMiwwLCJWXFxvdGltZXMgViciXSxbMiwxLCJcXGJvdCJdLFswLDIsIlxcdGV4dHJte2lkfV9WXFxvdGltZXMgZiJdLFsyLDMsInYiXSxbMSwzLCJ3IiwyXSxbMCwxLCJmXFxvdGltZXMgXFx0ZXh0cm17aWR9KVciLDJdXQ==
\begin{tikzcd}
	{V\otimes W'} && {V\otimes V'} \\
	{W\otimes W'} && \bot
	\arrow["{\textrm{id}_V\otimes f}", from=1-1, to=1-3]
	\arrow["{f\otimes \textrm{id}_W}"', from=1-1, to=2-1]
	\arrow["v", from=1-3, to=2-3]
	\arrow["w"', from=2-1, to=2-3]
\end{tikzcd}}
